annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11813/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11813/canvas/1/1908ed48-6e67-429e-9ca7-25b8153d62a7","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T14:41:19.219Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The seamstresses’ outfits resemble nurses’ uniforms. They <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW50662430 BCX2\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-00355.html\"><u>appear early</u></a> in <em>Phantom Thread</em>, but here, as Reynolds falls ill, the connection to the film’s medical theme rises to the surface. Alma will act as Reynolds’s nurse while he recovers. The House of Woodcock has been ill (haunted) for some time despite the presence of various “nurses.”&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-11813/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:661.747572815534,482.38305383936444,1253.168578993822,555.8340688437777"}}}]}]}]}